1982
Rutherford Cabernet Sauvignon
Estate Bottled
Grown in selected Napa Valley vineyards, the grapes
used in the Rutherford Cabernet all have that hint of
"Rutherford dust" which has been a characteristic of fine
Cabernet fruit from this area.
Cabernet Sauvignon is the premier claret grape of the
world. It is responsible for the renouned Chateau-bottled
red wines of Bordeaux.
Great care is taken in making this wine so that even
though each vintage has its own personality, the wine
always possesses the Beaulieu "house" character.
